This script will convert a collection of SNT measurements.csv files from SNT into 
a single .csv file that is easy to use in graphcrafting with tools like ggplot 
or PRISM.


The script will prompt users to locate a file in a main directory with 
subdirectories that represent cell measurements of neurite length from 
SNT Measurements.csv


An example directory path is below where variables are indicated by `var`
.../`timepoint`/`date`/`condition`/SNT_analysis/`cell`/SNT Measurements.csv


The length of each neurite, sum neurite length, and longest neurte/sum length
are compiled into 1 tidy dataframe then exported and used for graphcrafting.


Directions:
  1. Select a .csv files in the subdirectory of a single cell
  2. View the output files in the SNT_analysis directory
  